===Noun===
{{en-noun|~|currencies}}

# [[money|Money]] or other items used to facilitate [[transaction]]s.
#: ''[[wampum|Wampum]] was used as a '''currency''' by [[Amerindian]]s.''
# {{lb|en|more|_|specifically}} [[paper|Paper]] [[money]].
#* '''1943''', {{w|William Saroyan}}, {{w|The Human Comedy (novel)|''The Human Comedy''}}, chapter 3,
#*: Spangler went through his pockets, coming out with a handful of small coins, one piece of '''currency''' and a hard-boiled egg.
# The state of being [[current]]; general acceptance or recognition.
#: ''The [[jargon|jargon’s]] '''currency'''.''
# {{lb|en|obsolete}} [[fluency]]; readiness of utterance
# {{lb|en|obsolete}} Current value; general estimation; the [[rate]] at which anything is generally valued.
#: ''He {{...}} takes greatness of kingdoms according to their bulk and '''currency''', and not after intrinsic value.'' &mdash; Francis Bacon.
#: ''The bare name of Englishman {{...}} too often gave a transient '''currency''' to the worthless and ungrateful.'' &mdash; W. Irving.

